4 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 50-10.2-01 of the North Dakota Century Code is
5 amended and reenacted as follows:
6 50-10.2-01. Definitions.
7 In this chapter, unless the context or subject matter otherwise requires:
8 1. "Authorized electronic monitoringrecording" means the placement and use of an
9 authorized electronic monitoringrecording device, by a resident or resident
10 representative, in the resident's room.
11 2. "Authorized electronic monitoringrecording device" means video surveillance cameras,
12 monitoring devices, web-based cameras, video phones, or audio recording or
13 transmitting devices, or a combination of these devices,a device that is installed in the
14 room of a resident which are designed to acquire, transmit, broadcast, interact, oris
15 intended to record or is recording and transmitting video, communications, or other
16 sounds occurring in the room. The term does not include still cameras or devices used
17 for the purpose of the resident having contact with another person but not for the
18 purpose of electronically monitoring a resident.
19 3. "Conflict of interest" means any type of ownership in a facility or membership on the
20 governing body of a facility by a provider of goods or services to that facility or by a
21 member of that individual's immediate family.
22 4. "Department" means the department of health and human services.
